('00000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000201','notes-on-looking-twice','Notes on Looking Twice','What changes when a familiar image is given more time?','A sample paper about resisting the first, easiest version of a story.','Representation','[{"text":"This is sample editorial content created to demonstrate the reading experience. It does not represent a published claim or a completed paper by Daniel Koo."},{"heading":"The first image is rarely the whole image"},{"text":"Distance makes clean outlines. Real places are harder to hold: contradictory, ordinary, intimate, and always changing beneath the names used to describe them."},{"quote":"To look twice is to leave room for another person’s reality."}]'::jsonb,'2026-06-02T12:00:00Z','2026-06-02T12:00:00Z',7,'published','/editorial/paper-study.jpg',true),
